rr13jM6SUmfPPPGHHMHCgQ
This is my to go place for sushi. Although they raised their prices for all you can eat, there are no limitations that comes with it! Their deep fried and special rolls are tasty and savoring. The nigiri rolls are good but I could tell that the ahi was previously frozen and not as fresh as I wanted it to me. Believe me, I'm from hawaii and I know what fresh fish looks and tastes like.  Most of the workers are Japanese. They are very welcoming and the chefs at the bar are really funny. However, we did have a server name Brian than was really passive aggressive to our group. Be careful if you have him as a server, he might add a smart/witty remark about your order.   Overall I rate them a 4 because of the environment and authenticity. It's really hard to find a japanese restaurant that has japanese people as owners.

