I've been a regular for a year now. The quality of the fish is great. If you are looking for all you can eat and you are a nigiri sushi lover, this isn't the place to go. The reason being is that there are rules to ordering the sushi. There is a limit to how much sushi you can order. However, sushi sans quality and customer service is superb. This is a family owned company that has amazing food. If you love sushi rolls that are baked and everything else in between, CHECK THEM OUT! I recommend it!

